{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"788d86f6-e330-46b4-beaf-e7997f60558c","content":"It's a straightforward change. In your project file, simply **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- UseVSTest removed — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key things to know:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 already defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform**, so just deleting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is sufficient.\n2. **`dotnet test`** continues to work — the SDK wires up the new platform automatically.\n3. If you use **`.runsettings`**, most settings carry over, but review any VSTest-specific nodes.\n4. If you reference **`Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestPlatform.*`** packages directly, remove them — the SDK brings in the correct dependencies.\n5. Run `dotnet test` after the change to verify everything passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"264ab88c-d6d0-4995-9dba-88a69bab0acf","outputTokens":311,"requestId":"340E:81F2F:77A58E5:83E621F:69F3FAD9"},"id":"453f4869-4225-4a66-85a8-87f2ecab7e72","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:59:14.335Z","parentId":"95d49cfc-b932-4a27-b0cd-383cfd6a0368"}
